## Architecture & Data Flow

### Request lifecycle

```
Client request
  ‚Üí Express static middleware (serves frontend from frontend/dist/)
  ‚Üí x402 payment middleware (intercepts paid routes, returns 402 if no valid payment)
  ‚Üí Route handler
    ‚Üí agentServices.invokeAgentService(serviceId, input)
      ‚Üí service.handler(input) ‚Äî calls external API (e.g. Perplexity)
  ‚Üí Response: { serviceId, output: { ...service-specific fields } }
```

### Key abstractions

1. **`AgentService`** (src/agentServices.ts) ‚Äî Internal interface with `handler` function. Not exported.
2. **`AgentServiceDescriptor`** ‚Äî Public-facing service metadata (id, name, description, endpoint, schemas, payment terms). Exposed via catalog API.
3. **`PaidRouteDefinition`** ‚Äî Describes a paid route for x402 middleware registration (method, path, payment terms).
4. **`X402PaymentTerms`** ‚Äî Payment configuration per network: `{ scheme: "exact", network, asset: "USDC", price, payTo, facilitator }`.

### Service registry pattern

All services are defined in `createAgentServices()` in `src/agentServices.ts`. This function:
- Parses `X402_PAYMENT_OPTIONS` env var to build payment terms
- Returns an array of `AgentService` objects (each has a `handler` function)
- Is called fresh on each request (env vars are re-read)

Exported functions:
- `listAgentServices()` ‚Üí all service descriptors (for catalog)
- `getAgentServiceDescriptor(id)` ‚Üí single service descriptor
- `listPaidRouteDefinitions()` ‚Üí paid routes for x402 middleware
- `invokeAgentService(id, input)` ‚Üí execute a service handler
- `buildAgentManifest(baseUrl)` ‚Üí `.well-known/agent-services` manifest

## API Endpoints

| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET | `/health` | None | Health check (`{ status, uptime }`) |
| GET | `/agent/services` | None | Service catalog with payment metadata |
| GET | `/.well-known/agent-services` | None | Agent discovery manifest (absolute URLs) |
| POST | `/agent/services/:serviceId/invoke` | x402 (paid only) | Invoke a service |
| GET | `{*path}` | None | SPA fallback (serves frontend/dist/index.html) |

### Response format

Success: `{ serviceId: string, output: { ...service fields } }`

Errors: `{ error: "error_code", serviceId?: string, message?: string }`

Error codes: `invalid_service_id` (400), `invalid_service_input` (400), `payment_required` (402), `token_not_found` (404), `ens_not_found` (404), `service_not_found` (404), `upstream_request_failed` (502), `service_unavailable` (503), `service_execution_error` (500).

## Current Services

### 1. echo (Free)
- **Endpoint**: `POST /agent/services/echo/invoke`
- **Input**: `{ message?: string }` ‚Äî defaults to `"hello agent"`
- **Output**: `{ message: string, echoedAt: string (ISO 8601) }`
- **No payment required**

### 2. perplexity-search (Paid)
- **Endpoint**: `POST /agent/services/perplexity-search/invoke`
- **Input**: `{ query: string (required), model?: string }`
- **Output**: `{ answer: string, citations: string[], model: string }`
- **Price**: `X402_PRICE_PERPLEXITY_SEARCH` ‚Üí code default `$0.03` ‚Üí global `X402_PRICE` ‚Üí `$0.02`
- **Implementation** (`src/perplexitySearch.ts`): Calls Perplexity chat completions API (or OpenRouter as proxy)
- **Provider resolution**: `PERPLEXITY_API_PROVIDER` env var, or auto-detects based on which API key is set
- **Default models**: `sonar-pro` (direct Perplexity), `perplexity/sonar-pro` (OpenRouter)
- **Error classes**: `MissingPerplexityApiKeyError` (‚Üí 503), `PerplexityApiRequestError` (‚Üí 502), `AgentServiceInputError` (‚Üí 400)

### 3. token-price (Paid)
- **Endpoint**: `POST /agent/services/token-price/invoke`
- **Input**: `{ token: string (required), currency?: string (default "usd") }`
- **Output**: `{ id, symbol, name, price, currency, change24h, marketCap, volume24h, lastUpdated }`
- **Price**: `X402_PRICE_TOKEN_PRICE` ‚Üí code default `$0.0005` ‚Üí global `X402_PRICE` ‚Üí `$0.02`
- **Implementation** (`src/tokenPrice.ts`): Two-step CoinGecko lookup ‚Äî search by name/symbol/ID, then fetch price data
- **API calls**: `GET /search?query={token}` (resolve to CoinGecko ID) ‚Üí `GET /simple/price?ids={id}` (fetch price + market data)
- **No API key required** ‚Äî uses CoinGecko free tier (~10-30 req/min rate limit)
- **Caching**: Two-layer in-memory TTL cache ‚Äî search results cached 5 min (`searchCache`), price data cached 30 s (`priceCache`). Call `clearTokenPriceCache()` in tests to reset.
- **Error classes**: `TokenNotFoundError` (‚Üí 404), `TokenPriceApiError` (‚Üí 502), `AgentServiceInputError` (‚Üí 400)

### 4. ens-resolve (Paid)
- **Endpoint**: `POST /agent/services/ens-resolve/invoke`
- **Input**: `{ name?: string, address?: string }` ‚Äî at least one required; `name` takes priority
- **Output**: `{ name, address, avatar, records: { description, url, com.twitter, com.github, org.telegram, email } }`
- **Price**: `X402_PRICE_ENS_RESOLVE` ‚Üí code default `$0.0005` ‚Üí global `X402_PRICE` ‚Üí `$0.02`
- **Implementation** (`src/ensResolve.ts`): Uses viem `publicClient` on Ethereum mainnet to call ENS contracts
- **RPC**: `ETHEREUM_RPC_URL` env var, fallback `https://ethereum-rpc.publicnode.com`
- **Forward resolution**: `getEnsAddress()` + `getEnsAvatar()` + `getEnsText()` for 6 record keys
- **Reverse resolution**: `getEnsName()` + avatar + text records
- **Caching**: In-memory TTL cache (5 min), keyed on normalized input. `clearEnsCache()` / `resetEnsClient()` for tests.
- **Error classes**: `EnsNotFoundError` (‚Üí 404), `EnsResolveApiError` (‚Üí 502), `AgentServiceInputError` (‚Üí 400)

## x402 Payment Flow

1. **x402Middleware.ts** creates Express middleware via `@x402/express`'s `paymentMiddleware()`
2. It registers each paid route with its `accepts` config (network, price, payTo)
3. Uses `ExactEvmScheme` from `@x402/evm` for USDC payment verification
4. Payment verification goes through the configured facilitator (`X402_FACILITATOR_URL`)
5. Unpaid requests to paid routes get HTTP 402 with `payment-required` header
6. The `createApp()` factory accepts `enableX402` option (default: `process.env.X402_ENABLED !== "false"`)

### Multi-chain support
- `X402_PAYMENT_OPTIONS` is a JSON array; each entry has `network` (EVM CAIP-2), `payTo`, optional `facilitator`
- When multiple options exist, `paymentOptions` array is included in service descriptors

### Per-service pricing
Price is resolved per service via `resolveServicePrice(serviceId, serviceDefault?)`:
1. `X402_PRICE_{SERVICE_ID}` env var (ID uppercased, hyphens ‚Üí underscores)
2. `serviceDefault` (code-level default passed in service definition)
3. `X402_PRICE` (global env var)
4. `DEFAULT_X402_PRICE` (`$0.02`)

Payment terms are built per service in `createAgentServices()` via `buildPaymentTerms(serviceId, serviceDefault?)`.

## How to Add a New Service

1. Create implementation file: `src/myNewService.ts` with handler function
2. In `createAgentServices()`, add a `buildPaymentTerms()` call and service definition:
   ```typescript
   const myTerms = buildPaymentTerms("my-new-service", "$0.01"); // optional code-level default
   // ...
   {
     id: "my-new-service",
     name: "My New Service",
     description: "...",
     endpoint: "/agent/services/my-new-service/invoke",
     inputSchema: { type: "object", required: ["field"], properties: { field: { type: "string" } } },
     outputSchema: { type: "object", properties: { result: { type: "string" } } },
     payment: myTerms.primary,
     paymentOptions: myTerms.options,
     handler: async (input) => {
       // validate input, call external API, return output
     },
   }
   ```
3. If the handler can throw new error types, handle them in `app.ts`'s catch block
4. Add tests to `src/app.test.ts`
5. Update `frontend/public/llms.txt` (required by llms-txt-review rule)
6. Update `README.md`

**No route registration needed** ‚Äî the dynamic `/agent/services/:serviceId/invoke` route handles all services. Paid routes are automatically protected by x402 middleware if the service has `payment` defined.

## Frontend

Single-page React app with landing page sections:
- **Header**: Navigation with mobile menu
- **Hero**: Tagline with copy-to-clipboard
- **Features**: Feature highlights
- **Services**: Live service catalog (fetches from `/agent/services`)
- **Playground**: Interactive API testing UI (select service ‚Üí fill input ‚Üí invoke ‚Üí see response)
- **Footer**: Links

API client (`frontend/src/lib/api.ts`):
- `fetchServices()` ‚Üí `GET /agent/services`
- `invokeService(serviceId, input)` ‚Üí `POST /agent/services/:serviceId/invoke` (returns `{ status, body }`)

Vite dev server proxies API requests to backend on port 3000.

## Environment Variables

### Required
| Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `X402_PAYMENT_OPTIONS` | JSON array: `[{ "network": "eip155:8453", "payTo": "0x..." }]` |
| `PERPLEXITY_API_KEY` | Perplexity API key (when provider=perplexity) |
| `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` | OpenRouter API key (when provider=openrouter) |

### Optional
| Variable | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `PORT` | `3000` | Server listen port |
| `X402_ENABLED` | `true` | Set `false` to bypass paywall |
| `X402_PRICE` | `$0.02` | Global default price (USDC), used when no per-service price is set |
| `X402_PRICE_PERPLEXITY_SEARCH` | ‚Äî | Per-service price override for perplexity-search (code default: `$0.03`) |
| `X402_PRICE_TOKEN_PRICE` | ‚Äî | Per-service price override for token-price (code default: `$0.0005`) |
| `X402_PRICE_ENS_RESOLVE` | ‚Äî | Per-service price override for ens-resolve (code default: `$0.0005`) |
| `X402_FACILITATOR_URL` | `https://facilitator.payai.network` | Facilitator endpoint |
| `ETHEREUM_RPC_URL` | `https://ethereum-rpc.publicnode.com` | Ethereum mainnet RPC for ENS resolution |
| `PERPLEXITY_API_PROVIDER` | auto-detect | `perplexity` or `openrouter` |
| `PERPLEXITY_MODEL` | provider default | Model override |
| `PERPLEXITY_CHAT_COMPLETIONS_URL` | `https://api.perplexity.ai/chat/completions` | API URL override |
| `OPENROUTER_CHAT_COMPLETIONS_URL` | `https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions` | OpenRouter URL override |
| `OPENROUTER_HTTP_REFERER` | ‚Äî | OpenRouter attribution header |
| `OPENROUTER_APP_NAME` | ‚Äî | OpenRouter X-Title header |

